Anyone else get an error when using the spread operator within custom code actions? I have a base config I use with slight modifications and don't want to wind up modifying the original config which is a global variable.
```const BASE_CONFIG = {
    method: 'POST',
    hostname: '<http://api.HubSpot.com|api.HubSpot.com>',
    path: '/crm/v4/associations',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        Accept: 'application/json',
    },
};```
`const modifiedConfig = {...BASE_CONFIG, path} //results in Parsing Error, unexpected token ...`
